               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-128v: Large (ecclesial) Homiliary in Honor of the Monthly Feast of Saint Michael, arranged for the months of the year: Introduction (<locus target="#1r"/>), Ḫədar (<locus target="#8v"/>), Taḫśaś (<locus target="#23r"/>), Ṭərr (<locus target="#32r"/>), Yäkkatit (<locus target="#44r"/>), Mäggabit (<locus target="#50r"/>), Miyazya (<locus target="#68r"/>), Gənbot (<locus target="#76r"/>), Säne (<locus target="#81r"/>), Ḥamle (<locus target="#98r"/>), Näḥase (<locus target="#106v"/>), Mäskäräm (<locus target="#113r"/>), Ṭəqəmt (<locus target="#119r"/>). 20th century. Elaborate double-slip mahdar. Leather bound, then covered in fabric. F<locus target="#97v"/> and xxx mention Emperor Haile Selassie (1930-1974). <locus target="#1r"/> bottom mentions a secondary owner, whose name is written in blue ink. F<locus target="#22v"/> and passim mention the names of owner, ወልደ ሚካኤል, and his wife, ጸዳለ ማርያም. F<locus target="#50r"/> and passim mention the name of the scribe, ወልደ ዮሐንስ. The illuminations appear to be authentic.</summary>
